Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
When I select 'Female' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I select any Examination radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
Then I go to Page 03 and select 'Yes' in Contrast enhanced
Then I go to Page 06 of Pelvic MRI
And I click on 'Finding' radio button
And dropdown below 'Finding' is enabled

When I select 'Corpus uteri mass' from the dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Characterization I' tab is preselected
And 'I describe' button is preselected

And 'Orientation' localizer is enabled
And 'Axial (max.)*' input field is enabled
And 'Diameter of the endometrium' input field is enabled
And 'Diameter of endometrial - myometrial - transition zone' input field is enabled

And 'Fundus uteri' radio button is enabled
And 'Corpus uteri' radio button is enabled
And 'Isthmus uteri' radio button is enabled

And 'Mucosal/submucosal' checkbox is enabled
And 'Intramural' checkbox is enabled
And 'Subserous' checkbox is enabled

When I open the 'Orientation' localizer and click on any option
Then the option is is selected

When I enter '200' in the 'Axial (max.)* in mm' input field
Then 'Axial (max.)* 2nd plane orthogonal in mm' input field is enabled

When I enter '200' in the 'Axial (max.)* Diameter of the endometrium' input field
Then 'Axial (max.)* Craniocaudal in mm' input field is enabled

When I enter '200' in the 'Axial (max.)* Craniocaudal in mm' input field
Then the value is accepted

When I enter '200' in the 'Diameter of the endometrium' input field
Then the value is accepted

When I enter '200' in the 'Diameter of endometrial - myometrial - transition zone' input field
Then the value is accepted

When I select 'Mucosal/submucosal' checkbox
Then 'Pedunculated' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Pedunculated' checkbox
Then 'Length in mm' input field is enabled

When I enter '200' in the 'Length in mm' input field
Then the value is accepted

When I select 'Subserous' checkbox
Then 'Pedunculated' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Pedunculated' checkbox
Then 'Length in mm' input field is enabled

When I enter '200' in the 'Length in mm' input field
Then the value is accepted

When I click on 'Add new finding' button
Then new dropdown is displayed and enabled

When I select 'Corpus uteri mass' from the dropdown
Then 'Fundus uteri' radio button is enabled
And 'Corpus uteri' radio button is enabled
And 'Isthmus uteri' radio button is enabled

And 'Mucosal/submucosal' checkbox is enabled
And 'Intramural' checkbox is enabled
And 'Subserous' checkbox is enabled








